{
  "Comets are primarily composed of:": "",
  "Solid silicate rock and mineral fragments compacted together under moderate gravitational pressure over billions of years": "",
  "Dense metallic iron and nickel alloys similar to the composition found in the cores of differentiated asteroids": "",
  "Flowing liquid water maintained by internal heating processes, creating subsurface reservoirs beneath an icy outer shell": "",
  "Ice, dust, and rocky particles — often called 'dirty snowballs'": "",
  "Comets are mixtures of frozen gases (water, CO₂, methane), dust, and small rocky particles.": "",
  "A comet's tail always points:": "",
  "Directly toward Earth due to the gravitational attraction between the comet's volatile tail and our planet's mass": "",
  "Along the comet's direction of orbital travel, trailing behind it like exhaust streaming from a moving vehicle": "",
  "Away from the Sun, regardless of the comet's direction of travel": "",
  "Directly toward the Sun, pulled inward by solar gravity acting on the lightweight gas and dust particles in the tail": "",
  "Solar radiation pressure and solar wind push a comet's gas and dust tails away from the Sun.": "",
  "Most short-period comets originate from:": "",
  "The Sun": "",
  "The Kuiper Belt": "",
  "The asteroid belt": "",
  "Mars": "",
  "Short-period comets (orbital periods < 200 years) typically originate from the Kuiper Belt beyond Neptune.": "",
  "Long-period comets are thought to originate from:": "",
  "The Oort Cloud": "",
  "Jupiter's moons": "",
  "The Oort Cloud, a distant spherical shell of icy bodies extending ~50,000 AU, is the source of long-period comets.": "",
  "A meteor is:": "",
  "A solid piece of extraterrestrial rock or metal that survives atmospheric entry and lands on Earth's surface intact": "",
  "A streak of light caused by a small particle burning up in Earth's atmosphere": "",
  "A small icy body from the outer solar system passing through the inner solar system on a highly elliptical orbit": "",
  "A small solid fragment of rock or metal drifting through interplanetary space before encountering any planetary body": "",
  "A meteor (shooting star) is the visible streak of light when a meteoroid enters and burns up in the atmosphere.": "",
  "A meteorite is:": "",
  "A rocky body orbiting the Sun in the asteroid belt, typically several kilometers in diameter with an irregular shape": "",
  "A solid fragment of rock or metal traveling through interplanetary space that has not yet entered any planet's atmosphere": "",
  "A bright luminous trail produced when a high-velocity particle from space enters and ionizes atmospheric gases during descent": "",
  "A piece of space rock that survives passage through the atmosphere and reaches Earth's surface": "",
  "Meteorites are meteoroids that survive atmospheric entry and land on Earth's surface.": "",
  "Meteor showers occur when Earth passes through:": "",
  "The debris trail left by a comet": "",
  "A cloud of asteroids": "",
  "The Sun's corona": "",
  "Comets leave trails of dust along their orbits; when Earth crosses these trails, we see predictable meteor showers.": "",
